SIMPLE: procure
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Procure
<hw>Pro*cure"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Procured</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Procuring</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[F.
<ets>procurer</ets>, L. <ets>procurare</ets>, <ets>procuratum</ets>, to
take care of; <ets>pro</ets> for + <ets>curare</ets> to take care, fr.
<ets>cura</ets> care. See <er>Cure</er>, and cf. <er>Proctor</er>,
<er>Proxy</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To bring into possession; to cause to accrue to, or
to come into possession of; to acquire or provide for one's self or for
another; to gain; to get; to obtain by any means, as by purchase or
loan.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>If we <qex>procure</qex> not to ourselves more woe.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To contrive; to bring about; to effect; to
cause.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>By all means possible they <qex>procure</qex> to have gold and
silver among them in reproach.</q> <rj><qau>Robynson (More's Utopia)
.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Proceed, Solinus, to <qex>procure</qex> my fall.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To solicit; to entreat.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The famous Briton prince and faery knight, . . . ⟦br⟧
Of the fair Alma greatly were <qex>procured</qex>⟦br⟧
To make there longer sojourn and abode.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 1143 --></p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>To cause to come; to bring; to attract.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>What unaccustomed cause <qex>procures</qex> her hither?</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>To obtain for illicit intercourse or
prostitution.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- See <er>Attain</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Procure</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Procure
<hw>Pro*cure"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To pimp.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To manage business for another in court.</def>
<mark>[Scot.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Procurement</ent>⟦br⟧
